<TEXT>
Former Philippine first lady Imelda Marcos has 
asked the US government to allow her daughter into the United 
States for medical treatment a senator said Friday 
Sen Daniel Inouye DHawaii said Mrs Marcos visited his 
office here Friday morning and asked that the government drop a 
warrant for her daughters arrest 
Mrs Marcos has maintained Imee Marcos Manotoc is ill in Morocco 
and needs care in the United States 
Philippine officials have called Mrs Marcos plea an attempt to 
get Imee into the United States without having to testify against 
her father A grand jury in Virginia is investigating alleged 
corruption during Ferdinand Marcos 20year rule 
US officials have said Imee would be arrested upon arrival in 
the United States because she failed to answer a subpoena and 
appear before the grand jury 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

